okay i haven't really given anyone an insight into my head for a long time. so yea ya'll really wanna know what i'm thinking about...here it is. Those who say "you catch more flies with honey than with vingear" are retarded. Who the heck wants to catch flies they are so gross. I love flowers. they are the prettiest thing in nature. The main reason that i am such a "goody-two shoes" here is because 1.i am bound by reputation and 2.i dont want to disapoint my parents. I have learned that most of my morals and standards are circumstancial.i hold to them when it is very convenient for me. I really can't spell at all. sometimes that makes me feel really stupid. i play it off like its funny but most of the time its not to me. Somewhere in the back on my head, i really dont think that i will ever become a doctor. which really sucks. I still compete with katie all the time without wanting to. I am getting better but it is still hard. I want to be skinnier. I really think that is just a chick thing. I miss deep conversations. i miss one persons full attention. there is something about having someone's whole and undivided attention that makes you feel special. I am a B. sometimes i am in such a weird mood that the way certain people say my name grates my nerves. i feel bad for those people. they dont deserve it. i live in a fantasy world in my head. its easier and honestly i dont see anything bad about it. its so sad it really shows how much of a priss i am. i really wish that faries existed. they would be so pretty. i am so ready for college i could pop. i want new people and new surroundings. i love my friends i really do. they are the most important people in the world. I couldn't love them more. i suck at showing it but it is the truth. Things hurt me so much more than people think they do. its really easy to make me cry. although i will never cry in front of people. I miss summer so much. all this cold weather kills me. i miss volleyball and going down to the pier to the swing. everything just seems so much easier in the summer. i love the fact that i am southern. no offense to yankees but i absolutely love my heritage. in my moms words "they may have won the civil war, but we had prettier dresses." lol i love my mom. she's crazy. I am a horrible driver. i dont pay attention and i am lucky to have only gotten in as many wrecks as i have. i like to smile. it works the muscles in your face. anyway okay its like 1:30 and i am soooo tired. so i am going to go to bed now. peace out ya'll

   Katie's family is quite fun. they remind me alot of her. I have a new appreciation for lauren. she is really sweet and she takes really good care of katie even if katie doesn't see it. i miss my sissy. I don't know why katie is stressing out so much about that alabama thing. she'll get it done, she always does. I cant wait to go shopping tomorrow! i can only get one shirt because i am saving up for christmas and all but hey i get a new shirt. i was thinking about it today. my family really doesn't have a big  christmas and that always used to bug me when i was little. it doesn't anymore. we dont have a big christmas so we dont have to worry about money half way through jan. they don't feel like they have to buy my affection and plus with anna and my aunt staying at out house on christmas, it really isnt about me anymore. i love waking up to this precious little 4 year old pulling at my sleeve on christmas morning. i love seeing the look on her face. the innocence in a little child who still really believes without a doubt that santa is real is absolutely charming. im not the baby anymore, she is and christmas caters to her. i love it. people always told me that it isnt about what you get that matters but what you give. i didnt really get that till just a while ago. i am so exicted to give everybody their gifts. as much as i whine and complain and blow things out of proportion and am a complete brat sometimes... i am truely blessed. i couldn't ask for anything more in my life. what else could i want?
*~*irene*~*
